<s> This is a really good point:  </s>
<s> At risk of belaboring the obvious, I'd like to add that clients SHOULD check the ETag when doing a PUT request (it's just one extra header).  </s>
<s> This should be done even if the client things they've locked the file because locks can go away or (although wrongly) be used by another process owned by the same user.  </s>
<s> Thus, if clients SHOULD check the ETag before putting the file, it makes it even more important for servers not to change the ETag unless the contents have actually changed.  </s>
<s> Changing the ETag when the body is unchanged could result in a poor user experience, if their application has to pop up a dialog or return an error saying "The file you are trying to save MAY have been changed.  </s>
